#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Why are citizens’ assemblies necessary?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:44
msgid ""
"A functioning democracy should enable voters to decide the direction in "
"which their country moves. In theory, if citizens are not happy with this "
"direction, they can vote for change. In practice, however, democratic "
"governments favour solving short-term problems that ensure their popularity. "
"Governments bury difficult, controversial, or long-term issues, such as the "
"climate and ecological crisis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:46
msgid ""
"Setting up a citizens’ assembly addresses this problem: if the pressure of a "
"citizens’ assembly is larger than the pressure of a government’s supporters "
"and funders, action on climate change might be possible. The open discussion "
"of this huge and complicated issue can finally happen in a constructive and "
"fair way."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "How does a citizens’ assembly work?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:50
msgid ""
"Citizens’ assemblies must follow a carefully designed process. This is "
"incredibly important, because an ineffective CA could create the impression "
"that they’re a waste of time – it would probably be worse than not having "
"one at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:52
msgid ""
"Each CA differs depending on topic, location, and participants, but this is "
"the rough process:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:58
msgid "Select a clear topic and question that is suitable for deliberation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:58
msgid ""
"Establish a media budget large enough to ensure all people in the country "
"are aware of and engaged with the CA – this puts pressure on the government "
"to follow the CA’s final recommendations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:58
msgid ""
"Select coordinators. This should be an independent organisation with "
"experience in organising deliberative processes like citizens' assemblies."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:58
msgid ""
"Decide on the number of citizens necessary for a fair and representative CA."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:58
msgid "Choose demographics for a representative CA. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   * '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:68
msgid "Age"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   * '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:68
msgid "Gender"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   * '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:68
msgid "Occupation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   * '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:68
msgid "Ethnicity"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   * '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:68
msgid "Level of education"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   * Location\n"
"6. Create a media strategy to ensure everyone is aware that it is happening. For example, invite journalists, create a website, create a social media presence, etc.\n"
"7. Citizens are chosen using a random selection process, followed by a sorting process to ensure that the sample accurately represents the population as a whole (this is called 'sortition')\n"
"8. CA begins:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "   a. Integration stage\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "   b. Education stage\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "   c. Deliberation stage\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "   d. Recommendations stage\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:79
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   f. Voting stage: Recommendations approved when, for example, 80% agree\n"
"9. Publicly announce and publish results:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   a. Publicly list details of those in government who are responsible for action\n"
"10. Hold regular CA reunions to maintain pressure on government.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Spread the word"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:86
msgid ""
"Point 2 is essential: everybody should know about the citizens’ assembly and "
"how it has been organised, so that the public trust it. Otherwise, "
"governments may smile, nod, and agree with a CA, then ignore its "
"recommendations. If the nation is aware of the recommendations however, they "
"will be harder for the government to ignore. More pressure equals more "
"action."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:88
msgid ""
"A big media budget can fund substantial and ongoing news coverage. A "
"citizens’ assembly should scream and shout about its existence, so "
"everybody’s talking about it."
msgstr ""

