#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "Are citizens’ assemblies the same as people’s assemblies?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:96
msgid ""
"No. Extinction Rebellion also uses people’s assemblies (PAs), so it is easy "
"to confuse the two terms. Both encourage decision-making through "
"constructive conversation, but a people’s assembly does not have a selection "
"process; anybody can take part. PAs also don't have a learning phase led by "
"experts, nor detailed, critical thinking and learning at the beginning. A PA "
"can also be much shorter than a CA, such as a day or less."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:98
msgid ""
"For example, during an Extinction Rebellion protest with a growing police "
"presence, a PA can answer these questions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:102
msgid "Is it time to leave?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:102
msgid "Is it important to stay and call for more support?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:102
msgid "Is this protest still achieving our aims?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:104
msgid ""
"You can answer these questions in a fair, all-inclusive way with a people’s "
"assembly. Every PA participant states their opinion in a small group, "
"followed by deliberation, listening, and conclusions. Each group then "
"submits its conclusions and the assembly reaches a decision."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:106
msgid ""
"Extinction Rebellion does not have a leadership hierarchy, so people’s "
"assemblies are fundamental: PAs avoid top-down, undemocratic decision-making."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:108
msgid ""
"[Read more about people’s assemblies in this guide by Extinction Rebellion "
"UK](https://extinctionrebellion.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/XR-"
"PeoplesManual.pdf)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:109
#, no-wrap
msgid "Nations without democracy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:112
msgid ""
"Authoritarian regimes would not tolerate a citizens’ assembly. Meanwhile, "
"governments of many ‘democratic’ countries may commission a citizens’ "
"assembly that is simply a public consultation, with no real decision-making "
"power. What can we do about this?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:114
msgid ""
"[Extinction Rebellion’s Participative Democracy hub](http://partdem-media."
"wixsite.com/xr-partdemocracy/patho) uses peoples’ assemblies to tackle these "
"problems through a growing global network. The hub organises regular "
"worldwide People’s Assembly Marathons (PAthons), during which a wave of PAs "
"take place across several days. Interested politicians are invited, who may "
"absorb the ideas that they hear from citizens. Another possible outcome is "
"that the government will agree to a citizens’ assembly to stop growing waves "
"of PAs."
msgstr ""

