msgid ""
"Find more information, resources, and training details at XR’s Participative "
"Democracy Working Group: <https://partdem-media.wixsite.com/xr-partdemocracy>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Are any governments using citizens’ assemblies already?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:122
msgid ""
"Good news: there are already examples of government-led citizens’ assemblies."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:124
msgid ""
"Poland: [Gdańsk Citizens’ Assemblies](https://www.resilience.org/"
"stories/2017-11-22/solutions-how-the-poles-are-making-democracy-work-again-"
"in-gdansk/), 2016 onwards"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:126
msgid ""
"In the city of Gdańsk (population 350,000), the mayor must organise an "
"assembly of 56 citizens when a question proposed by residents attracts 5,000 "
"signatures. This began after the city government failed to effectively deal "
"with floods in 2016. Decisions made in these assemblies are binding."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:128
msgid ""
"Canada: [Citizens' Assembly on Electoral Reform](https://citizensassembly."
"arts.ubc.ca/resources/final_report.pdf), 2004"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:130
msgid ""
"161 citizens concluded that a new ‘single transferable vote’ system should "
"be implemented in the Canadian province of British Columbia. This conclusion "
"was then the subject of a referendum in 2005. 57.7% of voters were in "
"favour, but because at least 60% was required, no change was made."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:132
msgid ""
"Ireland: [The Citizens’ Assembly](http://citizensassembly.ie/en/), 2016-2018"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:134
msgid ""
"99 citizens debated several complicated topics, such as abortion rights, and "
"the challenges of an ageing population. Several outcomes included a "
"referendum on abortion rights, as well as a list of 13 recommendations on "
"how Ireland could become a leader in tackling climate change. The Citizens’ "
"Assembly returned in January 2020 to discuss social change in Ireland and "
"the advancement of gender equality."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:136
msgid ""
"France: [Citizen's Convention on Climate](https://www."
"conventioncitoyennepourleclimat.fr/en/), 2019-2020"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:138
msgid ""
"‘In a spirit of social justice’, 150 citizens attended a series of seven "
"weekend sessions to discuss how France should achieve a 40% reduction in "
"greenhouse gas emissions by 2030. The convention was a response to France’s "
"widespread and prolonged *mouvement des gilets jaunes* protests. At the time "
"of writing, [implementing the convention’s 149 proposals are causing "
"difficulties for President Emmanuel Macron](https://www.politico.eu/article/"
"emmanuel-macron-green-experiment-is-getting-out-of-hands) and a bill is due "
"to be presented in December 2020."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "A citizens’ constitution"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:142
msgid ""
"[Chile’s Constitution Referendum](https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/2020_Chilean_national_plebiscite) is a thrilling example of another way "
"to place citizens at the centre of decision-making."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:144
msgid ""
"On 25 October 2020, [78.24% of voting Chileans demanded a new constitution "
"for the nation](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/oct/26/chile-vote-"
"scrap-pinochet-constitution). This referendum followed almost 12 months of "
"continual, massive protests caused by the former constitution, which Augusto "
"Pinochet (Chile’s ex-military dictator) wrote to benefit the rich and "
"powerful."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:146
msgid ""
"This vote also declared that a group of nominated and elected citizens will "
"write the new constitution, which the nation will assess and vote on in "
"mid-2022."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:147
#, no-wrap
msgid "Global Assembly 2021"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:150
msgid ""
"Citizens’ assemblies are clearly growing in significance, because a global "
"version is being planned by [globalassembly.org](https://globalassembly."
"org/). Conducted online, Global Assembly 2021 will involve 1000 people "
"chosen via a lottery from around the world, taking place in the months "
"before the UN’s Cop26 climate change conference in November 2021. This huge "
"CA won’t have any power over governments but, if it’s managed well, the "
"final recommendations will be difficult to ignore."
msgstr ""

