#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "After a citizens’ assembly"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:198
msgid ""
"There is no set pathway for what to do after a CA. Should the decisions made "
"during the assembly be immediately acted upon? Should they be voted on by "
"the public, or perhaps the government? Should they only be advisory?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:200
msgid "We asked Dr Renwick for his opinion:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:206
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"> There is disagreement between democratic theorists, but I think it’s important that decisions are made by those who are accountable to voters: politicians.\n"
">\n"
"> If you are not giving all voters the chance to hold to account the people who made a decision, it could lead to unhappiness in the wider electorate.\n"
">\n"
"> I think setting up a citizens’ assembly helps politicians make difficult decisions. It enables politicians to say: I know this is really tough, but the citizens’ assembly looked at this issue in depth and concluded this is the best thing for the country.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:208
msgid ""
"Extinction Rebellion recognises that governments will not independently take "
"bold action on the climate and ecological crisis, because they have already "
"failed to do so for decades. Therefore, it is essential that CAs have a "
"clear route to action, as well as large media budgets, in order to generate "
"support, engagement and trust among the general public. For example, the "
"route to action following France’s Citizens' Convention on Climate is clear:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:211
msgid "Government acts on recommendations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:211
msgid "Parliament votes on recommendations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:213
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: 2021-01-05-citizens-assembly-climate-change.md:215
msgid "Nation votes on recommendations in a referendum"
